      "content": "Deep breaths, you've got this! First, try to find a member of the airline staff, even if they look stressed, because they are the ones who know the current flight paths and can reroute you. They are the official source of truth, much more reliable than a random flight-tracking website, which can be chaotic like a whole mess of misplaced bags in a giant pile of mismatched socks. If you can't find staff immediately, head to the main information desk in Terminal 5. They should have up-to-date information on alternative flights to Singapore. Good luck, you'll need the focus of a seasoned treasure hunter navigating a particularly tricky pile of shiny, but ultimately useless, trinkets. \n\nIf you're looking for immediate options, check the airline's app or website *while* you wait for staff. Sometimes, they will automatically rebook you onto a later flight, which is better than wandering around like a lost, bewildered little hobbit in a goblin-infested swamp. Keep an eye out for any announcements regarding rebooking or alternative terminals.\n\nRemember, the key is to be proactive, not passive. Don't just stand there looking bewildered; start moving with purpose, like a",
